01:12:15,463 --> 01:12:18,459
I saw them as a very questionable family.

957
01:12:19,004 --> 01:12:23,792
There would be no reason for them
to accept a stranger into their lives...

958
01:12:25,255 --> 01:12:27,541
..unless there was something to hide.

959
01:12:27,588 --> 01:12:29,413
That would be the only reason.

960
01:12:29,463 --> 01:12:32,545
Something was being hidden
and I didn't know what that was.

961
01:12:42,212 --> 01:12:45,873
When Beverly refused
to give her blood sample,

962
01:12:45,920 --> 01:12:49,003
I started to become suspicious.

963
01:12:49,046 --> 01:12:51,997
They knew that I wasn't Nicholas.

964
01:12:53,837 --> 01:12:55,957
Whatever I was telling them,

965
01:12:58,128 --> 01:13:00,083
they didn't believe a word of it.

966
01:13:00,130 --> 01:13:01,918
But they were good at not showing it.

967
01:13:04,004 --> 01:13:08,164
I mean, who wouldn't see it?

968
01:13:10,462 --> 01:13:13,459
That's about four, five years ago now.

969
01:13:13,545 --> 01:13:17,040
I remember in Spain,
Carey did everything for me.

970
01:13:19,420 --> 01:13:21,328
When I didn't know something, she told me.

971
01:13:22,545 --> 01:13:25,293
"You forgot everything
but you're going to remember it now

972
01:13:25,335 --> 01:13:30,491
and, you know, this was Mom at the place
we're living in with... Do you remember?

973
01:13:30,544 --> 01:13:34,952
Oh, this was Chantelle. You remember
Chantelle. That's your niece, my daughter.

974
01:13:35,003 --> 01:13:38,332
Do you remember that? Do you
remember that? Do you remember that?"

975
01:13:38,377 --> 01:13:40,285
Over and over and over again.

976
01:13:40,336 --> 01:13:41,533
That's Jason.

977
01:13:41,587 --> 01:13:44,334
She wanted to put it in my head.

978
01:13:44,376 --> 01:13:47,246
She wanted to put it in my head
so I would never forget.

979
01:13:48,337 --> 01:13:51,417
She just could not say it's not Nicholas.

980
01:13:51,461 --> 01:13:53,368
Did she believe it or not?

981
01:13:53,419 --> 01:13:54,747
If you asked me, I would say,

982
01:13:54,794 --> 01:13:57,460
no, not for a second
did she believe I was her brother.

983
01:13:58,545 --> 01:14:00,784
She decided I was gonna be her brother.

984
01:14:02,544 --> 01:14:04,867
It's like I woke up in a place where...

985
01:14:06,503 --> 01:14:08,824
Lies even bigger than what I did.

986
01:14:08,876 --> 01:14:10,453
You know, it's...

987
01:14:11,293 --> 01:14:16,201
they pretended as much as I did
and even more.

988
01:14:24,376 --> 01:14:27,743
I kept thinking about the kid,
Nicholas Barclay.

989
01:14:38,210 --> 01:14:39,620
At the time of his disappearance,

990
01:14:39,669 --> 01:14:43,163
he was living with Beverly
in the house on Swallow Street

991
01:14:43,209 --> 01:14:46,244
and his brother Jason
was also living there.

992
01:14:52,542 --> 01:14:53,869
Jason, Nick's older brother,

993
01:14:53,917 --> 01:14:55,624
when he moved into their house,

994
01:14:55,668 --> 01:14:56,912
that house changed,

995
01:14:56,959 --> 01:14:58,333
because before he got there,

996
01:14:58,376 --> 01:14:59,619
Nick and his mom

997
01:14:59,667 --> 01:15:01,410
seemed pretty close to me.

998
01:15:02,751 --> 01:15:04,375
She loved him to death.

999
01:15:04,419 --> 01:15:09,204
I mean, she loved him, you could tell...
She, she... He was the light of her life.

1000
01:15:10,209 --> 01:15:13,656
This guy moved in,
he was a bum, a drug addict

1001
01:15:13,750 --> 01:15:15,292
and he only cared about himself.

1002
01:15:15,376 --> 01:15:19,073
And when he got into that house,
it just made things that much more worse.

1003
01:15:19,126 --> 01:15:23,285
In fact, I think it even pushed his mom
into doing drugs herself

1004
01:15:23,334 --> 01:15:24,957
when he moved into the house.

1005
01:15:25,000 --> 01:15:28,117
That house just became
a volatile situation altogether.

1006
01:15:31,959 --> 01:15:33,582
I discovered from the police files,

1007
01:15:33,626 --> 01:15:36,195
a couple of months
after the disappearance,

1008
01:15:36,791 --> 01:15:39,162
that Jason had called the police

1009
01:15:39,208 --> 01:15:42,955
and said that his brother
had tried to break into the house.

1010
01:15:46,167 --> 01:15:48,454
Well, we see that kind of thing all the time.

1011
01:15:48,501 --> 01:15:51,746
People, people
are constantly doing stuff like that

1012
01:15:51,790 --> 01:15:55,038
to make people think that person's alive.

1013
01:15:58,541 --> 01:16:00,117
I started to put two and two together

1014
01:16:00,165 --> 01:16:03,118
and I thought something happened
inside that house to that boy.

1015
01:16:11,039 --> 01:16:14,076
I didn't need to be Columbo
to put all the pieces together.

1016
01:16:16,334 --> 01:16:18,407
They killed him.

1017
01:16:19,082 --> 01:16:23,076
Some of them did it, some of them knew of it,
and some of them chose to ignore it.

1018
01:16:29,832 --> 01:16:32,581
I wasn't worried about
Nicholas coming back no more.

1019
01:16:36,790 --> 01:16:40,155
Neither Nicholas Barclay
or his mother were cooperating,

1020
01:16:40,206 --> 01:16:43,538
so we were going to have to have
a search warrant executed

1021
01:16:43,583 --> 01:16:46,249
in order to obtain those blood samples.

1022
01:16:48,207 --> 01:16:52,782
I couldn't pretend no more to be Nicholas
and act like Nicholas.

1023
01:16:54,041 --> 01:16:57,487
I took two or three other agents with me
to go pick him up.

1024
01:16:59,124 --> 01:17:05,320
So inside me, I started getting,
you know, more and more aggressive,

1025
01:17:05,915 --> 01:17:07,193
weird.

1026
01:17:07,706 --> 01:17:09,329
I couldn't go on.

1027
01:17:10,124 --> 01:17:13,039
We got the fingerprints
and we got the palm prints.

1028
01:17:13,082 --> 01:17:16,944
Within a few weeks, we would be sending
them out to Interpol, to the embassies,

1029
01:17:16,997 --> 01:17:18,953
to see if any of these fingerprints

1030
01:17:18,998 --> 01:17:21,866
matched anything that they had on record.

1031
01:17:21,915 --> 01:17:23,704
I was trying to find a way out,

1032
01:17:23,791 --> 01:17:26,787
not only a way out in San Antonio, Texas,

1033
01:17:26,831 --> 01:17:29,035
but a way out, out of my mind.

1034
01:17:29,582 --> 01:17:32,946
Nicholas was becoming
much more agitated and angry

1035
01:17:32,997 --> 01:17:35,829
and I really felt like
he was going to run away

1036
01:17:35,872 --> 01:17:38,990
and if he ran away we might have
a very hard time locating him.

1037
01:17:39,833 --> 01:17:42,498
I started tailing him,
I started following him.

1038
01:17:42,539 --> 01:17:46,069
I started sitting up on Beverly's place
where she lived

1039
01:17:46,121 --> 01:17:50,281
and writing down licence numbers of
all the cars that came to her, to see her.

1040
01:17:52,206 --> 01:17:56,281
So I took a razor blade
and I slit my face.

1041
01:17:56,330 --> 01:17:59,494
Everything was snowballing
and snowballing and snowballing.

1042
01:17:59,539 --> 01:18:03,199
I show them, show them that

1043
01:18:03,246 --> 01:18:05,782
I was under a great deal of pressure.

1044
01:18:05,830 --> 01:18:07,867
On March 3rd of 1998,

1045
01:18:07,912 --> 01:18:11,659
the legate in Madrid, Spain, called me

1046
01:18:11,706 --> 01:18:14,490
and he said, "We've just identified him."

1047
01:18:14,539 --> 01:18:16,032
And I said, "You're kidding?"

1048
01:18:16,080 --> 01:18:21,200
I knew that everything was going down
and it was just a matter of weeks.

1049
01:18:21,247 --> 01:18:26,200
He said, "What I'm gonna do right now
is fax to you the records that I have."

1050
01:18:28,206 --> 01:18:29,863
CHARLIE: He agreed to meet with me.

1051
01:18:29,913 --> 01:18:31,785
We ordered hot cakes.

1052
01:18:32,245 --> 01:18:34,532
And we started to eat.

1053
01:18:34,579 --> 01:18:36,486
And he said...

1054
01:18:36,537 --> 01:18:38,909
I said,
"You really made your mother angry."

1055
01:18:38,956 --> 01:18:42,071
And he said,
"She's not my mother and you know it."

1056
01:18:43,039 --> 01:18:44,863
And I thought, well, I'II be damned.

1057
01:18:45,246 --> 01:18:47,487
And so I stood over the fax machine,

1058
01:18:49,246 --> 01:18:51,781
waiting for, of course, them to come in

1059
01:18:51,829 --> 01:18:54,068
because I was screaming
and jumping up and down.

1060
01:18:56,246 --> 01:18:58,237
I actually said, "Well, I'll be damned,

1061
01:18:58,288 --> 01:19:00,776
you're going to finally tell me
who you are."

1062
01:19:03,037 --> 01:19:07,280
I was like doing a dance
and everybody was high-fiving.

1063
01:19:07,329 --> 01:19:10,826
It was like, you know, we finally,
we finally know who this person is.

1064
01:19:13,037 --> 01:19:17,410
And my heart was beating fast,
just like it is now thinking about it.

1065
01:19:17,453 --> 01:19:20,866
And... And I said, "Who are you?"

1066
01:19:20,912 --> 01:19:24,075
He said, "I'm Frederic Bourdin
and I'm wanted by Interpol."

1067
01:19:27,036 --> 01:19:28,826
The fingerprint cards told me

1068
01:19:28,870 --> 01:19:32,201
that he was not 16, he was 23.

1069
01:19:32,827 --> 01:19:35,235
That he was not American, he was French.

1070
01:19:35,496 --> 01:19:38,494
That he was not Nicholas Barclay,
he was Frederic Bourdin.

1071
01:19:39,204 --> 01:19:42,153
We grow up in America thinking Interpol

1072
01:19:42,202 --> 01:19:45,783
is kind of the God of the cops.
You follow me?

1073
01:19:45,828 --> 01:19:48,399
That's the highest step you can get
in "Copland".

1074
01:19:48,453 --> 01:19:50,657
And so I thought, Jesus Christ,

1075
01:19:50,703 --> 01:19:54,069
if he's wanted by Interpol,
what has he done? You know.

1076
01:19:54,120 --> 01:19:56,109
There is no limit to what he's done.

1077
01:19:56,161 --> 01:19:57,702
So he began to tell me.

1078
01:20:01,161 --> 01:20:03,280
NANCY: Frederic Bourdin is delinquent.

1079
01:20:03,326 --> 01:20:05,402
Activities and modus operandi...

1080
01:20:14,287 --> 01:20:15,945
He has travelled throughout Europe

1081
01:20:15,995 --> 01:20:17,487
appearing at shelters for minors

1082
01:20:17,536 --> 01:20:18,993
under different aliases.

1083
01:20:19,827 --> 01:20:21,618
Spain, 1992.

1084
01:20:23,078 --> 01:20:25,400
Spain, September 1993.

1085
01:20:25,953 --> 01:20:28,026
(Overlapping voices)

1086
01:20:29,493 --> 01:20:30,523
Barcelona...

1087
01:20:30,576 --> 01:20:33,694
.. stated that he'd run away
from his adoptive parents' house.

1088
01:20:33,787 --> 01:20:35,860
Brussels, '95.

1089
01:20:38,119 --> 01:20:39,909
Pyrenees...

1090
01:20:39,953 --> 01:20:41,943
Milan, 1993.

1091
01:20:43,243 --> 01:20:44,440
Glasgow.

1092
01:20:44,493 --> 01:20:47,409
I sat there. I could hardly eat,
I could hardly swallow my food.

1093
01:20:53,203 --> 01:20:54,363
He always wore glasses.

1094
01:20:54,410 --> 01:20:56,566
Giovanni Petrullo.

1095
01:20:56,618 --> 01:20:58,692
Michelangelo Martini.

1096
01:20:59,243 --> 01:21:00,321
Donovan MacNeph.

1097
01:21:01,951 --> 01:21:03,361
- Peter Samson.
- William Thomas.

1098
01:21:03,410 --> 01:21:05,117
Jimmy Sale.

1099
01:21:05,162 --> 01:21:06,903
Peter Robin.

1100
01:21:06,953 --> 01:21:08,943
James Markey.

1101
01:21:08,994 --> 01:21:10,071
Frederic Cassis.

1102
01:21:10,118 --> 01:21:11,195
'93.

1103
01:21:13,409 --> 01:21:14,689
Hernandez Fernandez.

1104
01:21:14,785 --> 01:21:15,814
'95.

1105
01:21:15,867 --> 01:21:17,029
Edgar Guteyere.

1106
01:21:17,076 --> 01:21:18,356
'97.

1107
01:21:18,410 --> 01:21:20,484
Spain, 1997.

1108
01:21:20,783 --> 01:21:23,153
It's possible he may need psychiatric help.

1109
01:21:27,950 --> 01:21:29,277
Settle in tonight

1110
01:21:29,325 --> 01:21:31,283
because we are about to share with you

1111
01:21:31,327 --> 01:21:32,903
a story so bizarre,

1112
01:21:32,951 --> 01:21:35,026
it's hard to believe it's true.

1113
01:21:35,077 --> 01:21:37,612
This is the tale of a master imposter

1114
01:21:37,659 --> 01:21:41,025
who managed to lie his way
into the United States

1115
01:21:41,076 --> 01:21:44,442
and prey upon
the most vulnerable of people.

1116
01:21:44,493 --> 01:21:46,567
He is the only person in US history

1117
01:21:46,618 --> 01:21:50,149
ever to have assumed
the identity of a missing child.

1118
01:21:50,367 --> 01:21:53,152
He fooled even the lost boy's mother.

1119
01:21:53,200 --> 01:21:55,901
It's hard to imagine
how he could have gotten away with it.

1120
01:22:18,865 --> 01:22:22,812
We knew it was going to be,
you know, heart-wrenching and...

1121
01:22:24,116 --> 01:22:25,278
you know...

1122
01:22:25,324 --> 01:22:27,314
but we never thought it wouldn't be him.

1123
01:22:28,158 --> 01:22:30,528
You know, why would you even think that?

1124
01:22:30,575 --> 01:22:32,815
The first feeling was complete sadness.

1125
01:22:33,034 --> 01:22:35,522
Because it wasn't Nicholas.

1126
01:22:35,575 --> 01:22:37,565
Which took us back to square one.

1127
01:22:37,616 --> 01:22:39,940
Where is Nicholas?

1128
01:22:39,992 --> 01:22:42,066
That was the first one.

1129
01:22:43,658 --> 01:22:46,441
The second emotion was,

1130
01:22:49,242 --> 01:22:52,073
how could I be so fucking stupid?

1131
01:22:52,115 --> 01:22:53,939
I mean, seriously.

1132
01:22:57,907 --> 01:23:01,605
I contacted the SAPD,
the San Antonio Police Department,

1133
01:23:01,658 --> 01:23:05,816
and told them, decided to tell them,
that, hey, they killed him.

1134
01:23:09,783 --> 01:23:12,272
Based upon Frederic Bourdin's allegations,

1135
01:23:13,073 --> 01:23:16,653
a homicide investigation was opened

1136
01:23:16,699 --> 01:23:20,395
and the allegation
was against the family members

1137
01:23:20,448 --> 01:23:24,986
as being...participating in
the disappearance of the child.

1138
01:23:25,030 --> 01:23:29,524
It was related to us
that while Frederic was in jail

1139
01:23:29,574 --> 01:23:32,276
that he said that my mom confessed to him

1140
01:23:32,324 --> 01:23:35,274
that her and Jason
killed Nicholas and hid the body.

1141
01:23:37,490 --> 01:23:39,032
They accused me first

1142
01:23:41,449 --> 01:23:43,522
and it totally freaked me out.

1143
01:23:45,198 --> 01:23:50,565
Because I, I...have been crazy
but never violent.

1144
01:23:52,823 --> 01:23:57,446
This is the street the kid lived on
when he went missing.

1145
01:24:04,281 --> 01:24:06,355
There's the house right there.

1146
01:24:10,448 --> 01:24:12,354
I think the boy's buried here.

1147
01:24:14,906 --> 01:24:17,987
I want to talk to Darryl inside.

1148
01:24:18,030 --> 01:24:24,441
He's agreed to let me dig
and see if Nicholas Barclay's here.

1149
01:24:26,657 --> 01:24:29,440
If Beverly knew that this individual
was not her son,

1150
01:24:29,489 --> 01:24:32,321
then she had to have
some type of ulterior motive

1151
01:24:32,364 --> 01:24:36,357
and it had to be something very scary

1152
01:24:36,406 --> 01:24:40,103
for her to accept a stranger
into her household

1153
01:24:40,156 --> 01:24:41,613
posing as her own son.

1154
01:24:41,655 --> 01:24:43,776
I agreed to take a lie detector test.

1155
01:24:44,989 --> 01:24:47,062
She passed the polygraph.

1156
01:24:48,030 --> 01:24:51,229
And I said to the polygraph examiner,

1157
01:24:51,279 --> 01:24:52,938
"I don't understand this,

1158
01:24:52,987 --> 01:24:55,692
I don't understand it at all.
Will you give it to her again?"

1159
01:25:02,655 --> 01:25:06,067
So he gave it to her again
and she passed the polygraph.

1160
01:25:06,113 --> 01:25:09,147
I said, "No, there is something wrong."

1161
01:25:11,571 --> 01:25:13,645
The third time he gave it to her,

1162
01:25:14,865 --> 01:25:16,189
she flunked every question.

1163
01:25:16,237 --> 01:25:17,611
I mean, like, big-time.

1164
01:25:17,653 --> 01:25:21,517
The polygrapher said the machine
practically jumped off the table.

1165
01:25:22,321 --> 01:25:26,102
Her answers appeared to be
false on everything.

1166
01:25:29,780 --> 01:25:31,402
And he turned to her and he said,

1167
01:25:31,445 --> 01:25:35,854
"Mrs Dollarhide, it appears
that you know where your son is.

1168
01:25:35,905 --> 01:25:40,229
It appears that you know what happened
to him" and some other questions.

1169
01:25:40,487 --> 01:25:43,570
And that's when she became
very aggravated, very agitated,

1170
01:25:43,613 --> 01:25:45,437
jumped up and ran out and was screaming.

1171
01:25:48,778 --> 01:25:53,022
I lied about being...stealing,

1172
01:25:55,196 --> 01:25:58,194
and I had...so that's why I failed.

1173
01:25:59,029 --> 01:26:02,607
I didn't lie about anything
to do with Nicholas.

1174
01:26:02,653 --> 01:26:04,561
It was the other questions.

1175
01:26:05,987 --> 01:26:07,859
- Darryl? Charlie Parker.
- Mr Parker.

1176
01:26:07,904 --> 01:26:09,976
How are you doin'?

1177
01:26:10,445 --> 01:26:11,642
It's nice in here.

1178
01:26:11,695 --> 01:26:13,154
So this is the house, huh?

1179
01:26:13,196 --> 01:26:14,569
Yes, sir.

1180
01:26:14,611 --> 01:26:19,944
The polygraph led us to believe
that she did have some information...

1181
01:26:22,070 --> 01:26:26,195
..she could provide that she refused to
and we felt like Jason had information.

1182
01:26:26,862 --> 01:26:31,435
If Jason did something to Nicholas,
I didn't know about it

1183
01:26:31,486 --> 01:26:36,191
and I can't imagine Jason ever doing that.

1184
01:26:36,237 --> 01:26:38,605
It's just not in his makeup,

1185
01:26:41,779 --> 01:26:44,644
but...I don't know.

1186
01:26:45,611 --> 01:26:52,521
I know my brother or my mother did not
kill Nicholas, accidentally, on purpose.

1187
01:26:52,570 --> 01:26:55,106
Whatever Frederic said, it never happened.

1188
01:26:55,903 --> 01:27:00,643
When we first got my dog, he was always
digging in the back corner over there

1189
01:27:00,694 --> 01:27:02,068
where the, the tree is.

1190
01:27:02,111 --> 01:27:06,852
And one day I was mowing
and saw, like, pieces of, like, plastic,

1191
01:27:06,903 --> 01:27:09,308
- kind of like a tarp kind of material...
- OK.

1192
01:27:09,361 --> 01:27:12,228
..sticking out of the ground.
I tried to pull it up to get it out,

1193
01:27:12,276 --> 01:27:15,190
and it just kept ripping on me
as it was stuck in the ground.

1194
01:27:15,234 --> 01:27:17,806
So I never paid any attention to it
or gave it any thought,

1195
01:27:17,860 --> 01:27:20,267
until last night when we were speaking
on the phone.

1196
01:27:21,319 --> 01:27:23,523
And the bush has been there a while?

1197
01:27:26,610 --> 01:27:30,652
I had initially tried to get a hold of
Jason prior to Frederic's arrest

1198
